HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 245
By Hardaway
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Richard David Terrell,
Sr., of Shelby County.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Richard David Terrell, Sr., of Shelby County; and
WHEREAS, Richard Terrell was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Memphis on October 30, 1951, Mr. Terrell was the son of Goldie
and Vera Louise Foster Terrell; and
WHEREAS, Richard Terrell was a proud graduate of Millington Central High School; he
attended Christian Brothers University, graduating in 1973, and earned his doctorate degree
from Lighthouse Christian College in 2017; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Terrell was a leader in his community and was inducted into the Hall of
Fame at Millington Central High School and Christian Brothers University, honors that duly
recognized his life achievements and contributions; and
WHEREAS, a gentleman of many talents and interests, Mr. Terrell had an undeniable
love for horses and served several horse associations as an accredited judge; and
WHEREAS, Richard Terrell was deeply devoted to his family and friends, and he always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, he will be sadly missed but fondly remembered by his beloved wife of more
than forty years, Maria Teresa Terrell; his children, Derrick (Shirley) Terrell, Richard David
Terrell, Jr., and Laura Michelle (Tommy) George; his four grandchildren; and one great-
grandchild, whom he cherished greatly; and
